00:35:21.930 --> 00:35:22.690
they don't double.

00:35:22.690 --> 00:35:23.731
They actually quadrupole.

00:35:23.731 --> 00:35:25.355
You get about a 14% increase.

00:35:26.487 --> 00:35:28.070
So there's a really
good example of us

00:35:28.070 --> 00:35:30.860
responding to an obligation.

00:35:30.860 --> 00:35:32.795
Someone's given
that to us first.

00:35:32.795 --> 00:35:37.190
Now if every single
restaurant did that,

00:35:37.190 --> 00:35:39.960
we would very,
very quickly become

00:35:39.960 --> 00:35:42.940
desensitized to that
particular tactic.

00:35:44.040 --> 00:35:46.300
And therefore, I
think you would wane.

00:35:46.300 --> 00:35:49.070
It would decrease in
effectiveness pretty rapidly.

00:35:50.300 --> 00:35:54.760
But the fundamental
motive that drives

00:35:54.760 --> 00:35:56.960
that behavior, our
desire to give back

00:35:56.960 --> 00:36:00.360
to others what has been given
to us first and to live up

00:36:00.360 --> 00:36:03.420
or obligations, that
doesn't wane at all.

00:36:03.420 --> 00:36:05.510
So I think the answer
to your question

00:36:05.510 --> 00:36:08.130
is that the
individual strategies

00:36:08.130 --> 00:36:11.890
and tactics themselves
could become less effective

00:36:11.890 --> 00:36:14.190
over time, but the
fundamental set

00:36:14.190 --> 00:36:18.890
of principles that shape and
guide influence and persuasion

00:36:18.890 --> 00:36:23.310
will increase in value as
we become more information

00:36:23.310 --> 00:36:26.370
overloaded, more stimulus
saturated, and require

00:36:26.370 --> 00:36:28.820
these shortcuts
to good decisions.

