00:36:53.010 --> 00:36:55.580
and incentives aren't important.

00:36:55.580 --> 00:36:57.540
They are very, very important.

00:36:57.540 --> 00:37:00.390
But consider them--
consider them like this.

00:37:00.390 --> 00:37:02.420
Consider them like
two legs of a stool.

00:37:03.850 --> 00:37:06.600
Two legged stools
are often wobbly.

00:37:06.600 --> 00:37:09.270
What this set of research
presents and offers

00:37:09.270 --> 00:37:13.250
is a third stabilizing
leg, a third lever.

00:37:14.330 --> 00:37:16.920
and this thing
about information.

00:37:19.220 --> 00:37:22.000
It's great that we have access
to just so much information,

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:24.500
easily accessible at
the click of a button,

00:37:24.500 --> 00:37:26.120
the swipe of a screen.

00:37:26.120 --> 00:37:29.862
You are, as an organization,
the world's curators

00:37:29.862 --> 00:37:31.320
when it comes to
information, and I

00:37:31.320 --> 00:37:33.530
think that's an actual
wonderful thing.

00:37:33.530 --> 00:37:35.862
But remember too
that we are just

00:37:35.862 --> 00:37:37.070
overwhelmed with information.

00:37:38.430 --> 00:37:43.320
Just simply pouring more
information into an appeal

00:37:43.320 --> 00:37:47.230
is much like pouring more
water into an already full pail

00:37:47.230 --> 00:37:47.880
of water.

00:37:47.880 --> 00:37:49.379
It'll just spill
out over the sides.

00:37:49.379 --> 00:37:53.270
And so it's not information
the influences us.

00:37:53.270 --> 00:37:56.460
Its information in
the right context

00:37:56.460 --> 00:37:58.340
that aligns to one of
these core motivations.

00:37:58.340 --> 00:38:01.430
That, I think, is the key
to successful persuasion.

00:38:01.430 --> 00:38:07.542
It provides that additional
set of tools in that regard.

